  "bodyText": "## Mission\n\nThe Barbados Prison Service serves the public by keeping safely in custody those committed by the courts. Our duty is to look after them with humanity and help them to live law-abiding and useful lives in custody and after release. This is achieved through the deployment of dedicated, professional, highly trained and well-motivated staff, sound regimes and focused rehabilitative programmes.\n\n## Directory\n\n| Office | Telephone |\n| --- | --- |\n| Superintendent of Prisons | (246) 535-7304 |\n| Assistant Superintendent of Prisons (Head of Admin) | (246) 535-7327 |\n| Assistant Superintendent of Prisons (Head of Custody) | (246) 535-7328 |\n| Head of Operations | (246) 535-7362 |\n| Head of Female Prison | (246) 535-7349 |\n| Head of Medical | (246) 535-7380 |\n| Duty Manager | (246) 535-7359 |"
